An elderly woman lost control of her vehicle and drove into a home Wednesday afternoon, according to Clearwater Fire & Rescue. The woman lost control of the Kia she was driving, veered into a yard and then hit a house at 2783 Haverhill Drive around 2:39 p.m, the agency said in a news release. A photo taken at the scene shows a broken window and damage to the exterior of the home. Clearwater police and Clearwater Fire & Rescue responded to the crash. The elderly woman and her passenger were taken to Mease Countryside Hospital with possible minor injuries, the release said. No information was released on the residents of the home. This is a developing story. Stay with tampabay.com for updates.